      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libgcrypt is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Libgcrypt is a general purpose cryptographic library originally based on code from GnuPG.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nLibgcrypt before 1.12.2 sometimes allows a heap-based buffer overflow and denial of service via crafted ECDH ciphertext to gcry_pk_decrypt.(CVE-2026-41989)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libgcrypt is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "libgcrypt",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
